Basic Education Minister Angie Motshekga is expected to announce the date for a phased-in reopening of schools. JOHANNESBURG - Basic Education Minister Angie Motshekga and Minister of Higher Education Blade Nzimande are expected to announce decisions made regarding the 2020 academic year. The total number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in South Africa has risen to 5,350 with the death toll increasing to 103.